Utterance: Hi! Welcome back! How have you been since our last session?
Hey Ellie! I’ve been doing well. Finals are finally over, and I’m enjoying my time off before graduation.
That’s fantastic! How did your mindfulness practice go this past week?
I actually started practicing it daily. I’ve been doing it for about five minutes in the morning.
That’s wonderful! How has that impacted your stress levels?
I feel calmer throughout the day. It helps me focus better, especially when I’m working.
That’s great to hear! Have you noticed any specific situations where mindfulness has helped you?
Yes! When I start feeling overwhelmed at work, I take a few minutes to breathe and refocus. It makes a difference.
Excellent! It sounds like you’re really integrating mindfulness into your routine. Have you shared your experience with your girlfriend yet?
I did! She was really supportive and even mentioned wanting to try it with me.
That’s wonderful! Practicing together can strengthen your bond. How did that conversation go overall?
It went really well. I told her how I’ve been feeling a bit lost after graduation, and she reassured me that it’s normal.
That’s a great response from her. It’s important to have that support. How do you feel about your motivation now?
I still have my moments, but talking about it helped. I’m starting to feel more inspired to explore job opportunities.
That’s a positive shift! Have you started looking into any specific job roles?
I’ve been researching positions in marketing and management. I think those align with my studies.
That sounds promising! Have you considered networking or reaching out to any contacts in those fields?
I haven’t yet, but I think I should. I have a few connections from school that could help.
Networking can open many doors. Would you like to set a goal to reach out to a couple of people this week?
Yes, that sounds like a good plan! I’ll aim to contact at least two people.
Perfect! It’s a manageable goal. Now, how about your relationship? Any new developments since our last session?
We’ve been spending more time together, and it’s been great. We went hiking last weekend.
That sounds lovely! Outdoor activities can be a great way to connect. How did that experience feel for you?
It felt refreshing. Being in nature always lifts my mood, and we had some great conversations.
That’s wonderful! It seems like you’re both nurturing your relationship well. Have you faced any challenges recently?
Not really. We’ve been good at communicating, and I’m trying to be more open about my feelings.
That’s a healthy approach. Remember, it’s a continuous process. Is there anything specific you’d like to work on in your relationship moving forward?
I think just maintaining that open communication. I want us to keep growing together.
That’s a great goal. As you both navigate your individual paths, supporting each other will be important. Have you discussed future plans together?
A little bit. We talked about traveling more after graduation, which we’re both excited about.
That sounds exciting! Traveling can create lasting memories. Have you thought about where you’d like to go?
We’re thinking about a road trip along the coast or maybe even a trip to Europe someday.
Both sound amazing! It’s great to have those dreams. How does planning for the future make you feel?
It makes me feel hopeful. I love having things to look forward to.
That’s a positive mindset to have. It can help you stay motivated in the present as well. Is there anything else you’d like to discuss today?
I think we’ve covered a lot. I feel good about the progress I’ve made.
I’m glad to hear that! For our next session, we can check in on your job search and how your mindfulness practice continues. Does that sound good?
Yes, I’m looking forward to it!
Great! I’ll see you next time. Take care!
Thanks, Ellie! Bye!
